description: 2005-2007, Commander, 23d Information Operations Squadron, Air Force Information Warfare Center, Lackland AFB, San Antonio Piloted Global War of Terror Information Operations tactics used in Iraq. Coordinated Air Force team supporting net attack tactics development for Strategic Command; drove non-kinetic effects use in joint military planning. Led DoD’s only joint, globally distributed network defense exercise. Orchestrated first-ever Air Force network attack weaponization process Authored first Information Operations tactics targeting mobile communications integrating air, space and cyber forces for combined operations centers. 2004-2005, Assistant for Sensitive Operations, Office of the Under Secretary of Defense for Intelligence, Pentagon Provided Office of the Secretary of Defense oversight and guidance for intelligence operations, plans, and capabilities. Advised Secretary of Defense and senior officials on sensitive operations and programs. Advocated warfighter intelligence programs in multi-million dollar annual budget to Congress. Oversaw 1025+ monthly ISR operations fulfilling all combatant commander needs. Led coordination for DoD establishment of new joint intelligence centers and new ISR Command. 2000-2004, Chief, Reconnaissance Branch, Chairman of Joint Chiefs of Staff/J2 ISR, Defense Intelligence Agency, Pentagon Wrote all-source intelligence collection plans for all Pacific Command’s major intelligence problems. Managed military airborne and maritime ISR assets as DoD’s chief ISR collection manager; allocated assets among combatant commands. DoD point-man for ENDURING FREEDOM and IRAQI FREEDOM ISR plans and employment. Briefed the Secretary of Defense monthly on worldwide ISR activities.

description: 1999-2000 Student, Air Univeristy Maxwell AFB, AL Air COmmand and Staff College. 1998-1999, Director of Operations, Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadrons, Incirlick AB, Turkey and Souda Bay, Crete Coordinated and tasked all NATO’s Electronic Warfare activities as the EW Cell Coordinator and U.S. ISR Battle Manager in the Combined Air Operations Center, Vicenza, Italy for ALLIED FORCE. Directed operational reconnaissance missions supporting allied efforts in/around the Balkans and in/around Iraq. Commanded reconnaissance unit during deployment to support NORTHERN WATCH operations over northern Iraq. 1995-1998, Commander, Operational Test and Evaluation EW Flight, 343 Reconnaissance Squadron, 55th Wing, Offutt AFB, Nebraska Directed comprehensive roadmap integrating leading edge EW technology, a multi-million dollar effort, into reconnaissance aircraft to include designing the tools, training, courseware development, and flight profiles for hundreds of crew members. Authored innovative EW support standards for SOUTHER WATCH operations over Iraq; integrated deployed Electronic Combat assets with novel communications procedures. Flew 4,000 hours of operational reconnaissance missions as EW squadron’s top crew commander, tactical coordinator and standardization evaluator. 1993-1995, Director, EW Mission Analysis, 19th Squadron, 6th Fighter Wing, Riyadh AB, Royal Saudi Air Force Advised Royal Saudi Arabian Air Force members as part of the U.S. Military Training Mission on Electronic Warfare operations, training, flight examination, mission management, and tactics; created Saudi EW squadron from scratch. Evaluated all Saudi EW training courses and EW management procedures. 1987-1993, Chief, Flight EW Instructor Training, 343 Reconnaissance Squadron, 55th Wing, Offutt AFB, Nebraska Flew over 100 combat hours during DESERT STORM as EWO. Developed new procedures and tactics to integrate strategic reconnaissance assets into tactical combat operations.
